cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Syndesis: an evidence-concordant, interaction-constrained workflow for EGFR ATP-site analog design"
abstract: >-
  Syndesis is a reproducible, leakage-audited, structure-based cheminformatics
  workflow for EGFR ATP-site analog design that accepts a candidate only when
  independent structural evidence (docked pose, ProLIF interaction fingerprint,
  a leakage-controlled pose-confidence model, and short molecular-dynamics
  pose-stability) agrees on the validated binding mode, operationalizing and
  detecting docking-score hacking. Includes a feasibility comparison of an
  LLM-agent analog-design loop against a deterministic rule-based baseline.
type: software
authors:
